    <statement><div><p>
A cone has a perpendicular height of <m>{20}\,\text{cm}</m> and a slant height of
<m>{25}\,\text{cm}</m>. Take <m>\pi = \frac{22}{7}</m>.
</p>
<p>
Determine the following:
</p>

<ol type="i">
  <li><p>the radius of the cone</p>
   <p><m>\text{Radius}=</m><fillin characters="7" name="ans1"/><m>\,\text{cm}</m></p>
     </li>
  <li><p>the volume of the cone to the nearest whole numbers</p>
   <p><m>\text{Volume}=</m><fillin characters="7" name="ans2"/><m>\,\text{cm}^3</m></p>

    </li>
</ol></div></statement>
    <solution><div><p>
The cone has a perpendicular height of <m>{20}\,\text{cm}</m> and a slant height of
<m>{25}\,\text{cm}</m>.
</p>

<p><alert>Step 1: Determine the radius of the cone</alert></p>

<p>
For a cone, the radius <m>r</m>, the perpendicular height <m>h</m>, and the slant height <m>l</m>
form a right-angled triangle.
</p>

<p>
<md>
<mrow>l^2 \amp = r^2 + h^2</mrow>
</md>
</p>

<p>
Substituting the given values:
</p>

<p>
<md>
<mrow>({25})^2 \amp = r^2 + ({20})^2</mrow>
<mrow>r^2 \amp = ({25})^2 - ({20})^2</mrow>
<mrow>r^2 \amp = {25}^2 - {20}^2</mrow>
<mrow>r \amp = \sqrt{{25}^2 - {20}^2}</mrow>
<mrow>\amp ={15} \,\text{cm}</mrow>
</md>
</p>



<p><alert>Step 2: Find the volume of the cone</alert></p>

<p>
The formula for the volume of a cone is:
</p>

<p>
<md>
<mrow>V \amp = \frac{1}{3} \times \text{base area} \times \text{height}</mrow>
<mrow>\text{Base area} \amp = \pi r^2</mrow>
<mrow>\amp = \frac{22}{7} \times ({15})^2</mrow>
<mrow>\amp ={\frac{4950}{7}}\,\text{cm}^2</mrow>
</md>
</p>

<p>Therefore,<br/>

<md>
<mrow>V \amp = \frac{1}{3} \times {\frac{4950}{7}}\times {20}</mrow>
<mrow>\amp =\frac{1}{3} \times {\frac{99000}{7}}</mrow>
<mrow>\amp ={\frac{33000}{7}}</mrow>
<mrow>\amp ={4714}\ \text{cm}^3</mrow>
</md>
</p>

<p>
Rounded to the nearest whole number:
<br/>
<md>
<mrow>V \amp = {4714}\ \text{cm}^3</mrow>
</md>
</p>

<p>
Therefore:
</p>

<ol type="i">
  <li>
    <p>The radius of the cone is <m>{15}\,\text{cm}</m>.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>The volume of the cone is <alert><m>{4714}\,\text{cm}^3</m></alert>.</p>
  </li>
</ol></div></solution>
    <answer><p><m>15</m></p></answer>
    <answer><p><m>4714</m></p></answer>
